00:06:13.330 --> 00:06:20.160
Earlier you mention a developer that wants to hide his StopLoss 
 /TakeProfit , what did you mean by that ?

00:06:20.157 --> 00:06:26.610
Well, many traders suspects the broker to manipulate the feed 
 in order to catch trades and close them

00:06:26.612 --> 00:06:33.660
so smart EA writers keep the real StopLoss inside the code, 
 this would prevent the trade closing as we spoke

00:06:33.660 --> 00:06:41.770
but in case the EA terminal is disconnected from some technical 
 reason, a single trade can wipe the entire account.

00:06:41.768 --> 00:06:46.670
aha, This is a bit dangerous no?,  do you 
 have any tip how to avoid that ?

00:06:46.674 --> 00:06:54.990
What I usually do Is to set a false StopLoss which 
 is at least twice as far as my real StopLoss,

00:06:54.987 --> 00:07:00.330
 and I code my EA to close the 
 Trade when the real StopLoss is reached.

